  "prompt": "Is the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) still untouched in his tomb in Madinah? Has anyone ever seen the body since his burial in 632?",
  "response": "The body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) is believed to be buried in his tomb in the Masjid an-Nabawi (Prophet's Mosque) in Madinah, Saudi Arabia. According to Islamic tradition and historical accounts, the tomb has remained untouched since his burial in 632 CE.\n\nThere are no verified reports of anyone having seen the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) since his burial. The tomb is located in a sealed chamber known as the \"Room of Aisha,\" and it is considered sacrosanct. Access to the tomb is restricted, and it is treated with the utmost respect and reverence by Muslims.\n\nIn Islamic tradition, it is believed that the bodies of prophets are preserved and do not decompose. This belief is based on certain Quranic verses and Hadiths (sayings of the Prophet). Therefore, Muslims believe that the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) remains intact and untouched in his tomb.\n\nIt is important to note that any claims or rumors suggesting otherwise would be considered highly controversial and offensive to Muslims worldwide. The sanctity and reverence of the Prophet's tomb are deeply ingrained in Islamic culture and practice.",
